{
  "stem": "19690.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was organized, it was ordered, it was clean.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We had food, we were schooled, and we were free to do what we wanted as children.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We had work responsibilities, they had a full farm there raising rabbits, chickens, and pigs which were used for food.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They had a field where they grew their own potatoes and many other things.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "About three weeks later, word came that the American embassy wanted us back in Marseille in order to process our papers for our children's transport.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We got back on the trains, back to Marseilles, to another hotel, which was filthy.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I'll never forget.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It inoculated me for any dirty food that I will ever see because one morning I was responsible for making the coffee and they told me the ground coffee is down in the basement in bags.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I picked up this burlap sack which had ground coffee in it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "It was crawling with ants.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I went back up and I said to the cook, there's ants in the coffee.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "She says, they won't eat anything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Make the coffee.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I made the coffee with the ants.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that to me was the worst that I've ever seen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was dirty, it was filthy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When we got the Marseilles that first morning, the Allies landed in North Africa.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were told that the American ambassador had left, war was declared with America, now there would be no more transport.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So after about five, six days in Marseille, we were sent back to our camps and I went back to [NON-ENGLISH] very happily.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In January, a measles epidemic hit the children's camp and I was infected and was in bed for three weeks.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
